description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4 x CESR Competency Development Posts in General Adult Psychiatry&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;(Specialty Doctor level) - Blackpool/Fylde&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After the success of our Old Age CESR posts we are now really pleased to launch our General Adult Psychiatry CESR posts. These posts are tailored for those who prefer to develop their career via a different route with support from our learning organisation. The posts will be based on the Fylde Coast.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These exciting new posts will enable you to rotate through various jobs (including inpatients) over 2-3 years. This flexibility will allow us to tailor the posts to your progression and development needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This opportunity is designed to support you in broadening skills in adult psychiatry and developing the necessary competencies to successfully achieve CESR status. As such, the Trust will support the post holder through the following commitments:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2 sessions SPA time as standard&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The post holder will receive a structured portfolio in which to store WPBAs and other evidence for including in your CESR submission to the General Medical Council (GMC)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The post holder will be provided with additional resources to support learning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The post holder will receive regular clinical supervision (formal/informal) (weekly)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participation in weekly local MRCPsych programme guaranteed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free access to the RCPsych CPD Online&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to appropriate study budget&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunities for involvement with medical student teaching&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SAS Tutor support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attendance at CESR / SAS support forums&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunities for management / leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Special interest sessions can be arranged where agreed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trust accommodation within the Preston area is available for a fee if needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to the library facilities in the Lantern Centre&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details please see the attached example Job Description.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Mark Worthington&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deputy Medical Director&lt;/p&gt;
